<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-27T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">741.6111/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Polish Government in Exile</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-27T12:00:00+02:00">April 27,
                                    1942—12 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Polish Series 42. Supplementing my No. 41, April 27, 7 p.m. As pointed
                            out in my No. 34, April 24, 6 p.m. both Sikorski and Raczynski
                            originally intended to couch the Polish Government’s reply (Polish note
                            of April 21) to Eden’s note of April 17 in more conciliatory tone than
                            that adopted by Sikorski in his letter of April 16. However, the mood of
                            the Polish National Council during its session of April 21 was such that
                            Sikorski and Raczynski found it necessary to take a strong line.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>